title: Defending champ falls in Super League opener
text:
Defending champ falls in Super League opener By: Uncredited Report Error 
The defending Westman Super League of Curling champion started the new season on the wrong foot. 
Jerry Chudley gave up an early steal of two and then a three in the sixth end as he fell 8-6 to Cale Dunbar at the Brandon Curling Club on Wednesday night. 
Meanwhile, Terry McNamee and his new team scored back-to-back deuces in the first two ends to top Tyler Waterhouse 7-2 in six ends in their game while Steve Irwin, who played with McNamee last season, defeated Curtis McCannell 5-2. 
In the other games, Kelly Marnoch edged Shawn Taylor 6-5, Duane Lang scored one in the eighth to slip past Butch Mouck 5-4 and Kelly McMechan beat Perry Fisher 5-1 in six ends.
